    "created_at": "2013-01-08T19:16:08Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-01-08T19:16:08Z",
    "body": "Let me put it this way:\r\n\r\n1. A reasonable default behavior would be for SublimeClang to automatically include ALL code files in a project.\r\n\r\n2.  Another reasonable default behavior would be for SublimeClang to include NO code files from a project.  This would force users to always create a per-project settings file, which is annoying.  But it's logically coherent.\r\n\r\nWhat SublimeClang currently does is neither of these options.  It unpredictably includes SOME code files from a project, in a way that isn't obvious or consistent.  \r\n\r\nI would urge #1 or #2.\r\n\r\nIf you choose #2, I would ask you to make project-settings level settings _additive_ to per-user settings, rather than overwrite them.  This lessens the burden on users having to recreate _all_ their settings in every project they have. "
  },
