    "updated_at": "2013-01-08T20:26:54Z",
    "body": "I see you've pointed me to the code for parsing options (line 1179), but i'm not sure which part of it you're drawing my attention to.\r\n\r\nViewing things from an end-user perspective, can you help me understand what logic behing the current behavior is?  In my usage so far it seems that SublimeClang is (by default) only aware of the files at project's top level -- is that right?  Or at the same level as the .sublime-project file itself, wherever that is?  \r\n\r\nIf that's the case, I'm not sure that's the best option for a default, so i'd like to argue for other approaches.\r\n\r\n\r\n"
